<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Deploy Operations Bridge Suite</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 19 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Before you start configuring the suite, you must change the permissions for the output folder in the EFS share for the BVD container.
</p>
<ol><li>Go to the <code>mnt/efs/var/vols/itom/core/suite-install/opsbridge/output</code> directory.</li>
<li>Run the following command:
<pre>chown 1999:1999 bvd log</pre>
<b>Note:</b> These steps are required from Operations Bridge 2018.08 as the BVD container does not run as root user.</li></ol>
<p>After the ITOM CDF is deployed on the master nodes, you can deploy the Operations Bridge on ITOM CDF.
</p><p>Perform the following steps in the <b>Configure and Deploy</b> phase to deploy Operations Bridge:
</p>
<hr>
<p><b>Important</b><br>
</p><p>During the suite configuration, do not use any browser buttons (such as Back or Refresh) on the current installation wizard page; otherwise, unexpected errors might occur.
</p>
<hr>
<p><br>
</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Configure the suite defaults. The Suite Defaults configuration defines general settings that all capabilities of the suite share.</p></li>
