<h4><span id="Suite_Defaults_>_Configuration_Type"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Suite_Defaults_.3E_Configuration_Type">Suite Defaults &gt; Configuration Type</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Suite Defaults > Configuration Type">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Suite Defaults > Configuration Type">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Select the configuration type of the suite.<br>
<b>Custom configuration:</b> <i>Default</i>. Displays the complete configuration wizard. You can specify custom values for all capabilities.<br>
<b>Express configuration:</b> Uses default values for some of the settings, to speed up the configuration process. When this option is chosen, the suite by default uses an internal PostgreSQL database, a TLS certificate automatically generated by the Management Portal, a 60-day evaluation license, and the same password for the administrator and the PostgreSQL database user. The Management Pack for Infrastructure is installed automatically.</p>
<h4><span id="Suite_Defaults_>_Login"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Suite_Defaults_.3E_Login">Suite Defaults &gt; Login</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=2" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Suite Defaults > Login">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Suite Defaults > Login">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Define the default administrative user credentials for all capabilities.<br>
If you chose the express configuration, this will be the global password. <br>
If you chose the custom configuration, you can later specify individual user credentials for the different capabilities.</p>
<p><b>Login: </b>The login name is admin.<br>
<b>Password: </b>Specify a password for the administrator user. You can change this password again after the installation. </p></ol>
<ol>
<p>Note: The password must consist of eight characters or more, and contain at least one upper-case letter, one lower-case letter, one digit, and one special character.<br>
<b>Confirm password</b>: Re-enter your password.</p>
<h4><span id="Suite_Defaults_>_Connection"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Suite_Defaults_.3E_Connection">Suite Defaults &gt; Connection</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=3" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Suite Defaults > Connection">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Suite Defaults > Connection">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Specify your load balancer information. The load balancer is used to access the different user interfaces of the <span class="_HPc_Basic_Variables_HP_Product_Name">Operations Bridge Suite</span> capabilities.<br>
<b>External hostname: </b>The external hostname of the load balancer. This hostname must be resolvable via the DNS server, not only via /etc/hosts.<br>
<b>Port number: </b>The port of the load balancer. Default: 443<br>
<b>TLS certificate file: </b>Click <b>Use the certificate generated by the ITOM platform </b>to use the automatically generated certificate file. Click <b>Upload certificate</b> to browse your files and select the load balancer's server and CA root certificate files. The Operations Bridge Suite supports server certificates in P12 and PFX format, and CA certificates in PEM format.</p>
<li><p><i>Optional</i>. Configure Operations Bridge Manager (<span class="OMiOMi short">OBM</span>).<br>
</p></li>
<h4><span id="Jmx_>_Login"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="Jmx_.3E_Login">Jmx &gt; Login</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=4" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Jmx > Login">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Jmx > Login">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p><b>JMX Login:</b> This is your JMX username which is <b>admin</b>. <br>
</p>
<p>Set the password for the JMX admin user.<br>
<b>JMX password:</b> Type the JMX password. The password must be at least 8 characters and must contain at least one lower case [a - z], one upper-case [A - Z], at least one digit [0 - 9], and at least one special character.<br>
<b>Confirm password: </b> Retype the password.</p>
<h4><span id="OBM_>_Database_-_General"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="OBM_.3E_Database_-_General">OBM &gt; Database - General</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=5" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: OBM > Database - General">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: OBM > Database - General">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Configure a database to store all <span class="OMiOMi short">OBM</span> related information. You can choose to use the database specified earlier for CDF, use an <span class="OMiOMi short">OBM</span> specific internal database, or you can connect to an already existing database.<br>
<b>Use suite defaults: </b>Select to use the database that you specified during the CDF configuration. You have to specify the names of the Management, RTSM, and Event schemas.<br>
<b>Custom configuration: </b>Select to create a new database for this OBM instance or connect to an existing database.<br>
If you decide to use a remote database instance, you must preconfigure it according to the database requirements.<br>
If you decide to use an internal PostgreSQL database instance, OBM installs and configures the instance for you.</p>
<p><b>Database Type: </b>Select the appropriate database type: Internal PostgreSQL, External PostgreSQL, or Oracle. If you configure OBM with an external PostgreSQL, you have to create an additional database user with "create" permissions.<br>
<b>Host: </b>The name of the host machine on which the database is installed. Alternatively, you can also specify the IP address of the host machine.<br>
<b>Port number</b>: The database listening port. Default: 5432 (Postgres)<br>
<b>Login</b>: The name of a user with administrative permissions on the specified database.<br>
<b>Password</b>: The password of the specified user.<br>
<b>Use SSL</b>: Optional. Click <b>Use SSL</b> to encrypt the communication with the database. The server must be running with SSL communication enabled and it must provide a certificate for use by OBM.<br>
<b>SID</b>: Oracle System ID. Only required if you select SID instead of Connection String.<br>
<b>Connection String</b>: Oracle connection string. Only required if you select Connection String instead of SID.<br>

</p><h4><span id="OBM_>_Database_-_Settings"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="OBM_.3E_Database_-_Settings">OBM &gt; Database - Settings</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=6" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: OBM > Database - Settings">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: OBM > Database - Settings">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Enter the database names.<br>
<b>Management</b>: For storage of system-wide and management-related metadata. The default value is <b>mgmt</b>.<br>
<b>RTSM</b>: For storage of RTSM data. The RTSM (Run-time Service Model) is OBM's embedded CMDB, which acts as the central repository for configuration information that is collected and updated from the various OBM data collection processes. The default value is <b>rtsm</b>.<br>
<b>Event: </b>For storage of events and related data, such as annotations, as well as for storage of configuration data, such as event correlation rules. The default value is <b>event</b>.<br>
<br>
</p>
<p class="mw-empty-elt"></p>
<h4><span id="OBM_>_High_Availability"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="OBM_.3E_High_Availability">OBM &gt; High Availability</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=7" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: OBM > High Availability">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: OBM > High Availability">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Decide if you want to enable high availability for OBM by using two worker nodes for automatic failover.<br>
<b>Enable high availability for OBM</b>: Tick the checkbox to enable HA for OBM. Note that you should only set up high availability if you have at least two worker nodes and three master nodes. For more information on high availability, <a href="./itom/Operations_Bridge:2018.05_Premium/Configure-scaling-and-high-availability_22184510" title="Operations Bridge:2018.05 Premium/Configure-scaling-and-high-availability 22184510"> Configure high availability</a> .<br>
<span><span>It is currently not possible to unconfigure high availability for OBM once it has been enabled and deployed.</span><br>
</span></p>
<h4><span id="OBM_>_Management_Packs"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="OBM_.3E_Management_Packs">OBM &gt; Management Packs</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=8" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: OBM > Management Packs">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: OBM > Management Packs">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Select the <span class="OMiOMi short">OBM</span> Management Packs to install in your <span class="OMiOMi short">OBM</span> environment. <br>
You can choose not to install dependent management packs. However, if you do so, the functional scope of the selected management packs might be reduced.<br>
<b>Note</b>: Select <b>OBM Management Pack for VMWare Infrastructure</b> management pack if you have selected to install the <b>Virtualization Collector</b> capability. <br>
Management packs provide add-on content on top of OBM. They deliver automatic and end-to-end monitoring solutions of infrastructure and applications. Management packs enable users to monitor, detect, troubleshoot, and remediate issues in the IT domain. They increase the productivity of users by optimizing and automating various tasks, and reduce the mean time to resolve (MTTR) incidents.</p>
<p>Management packs discover application domains and proactively monitor the domains for availability and performance issues. They include, for example, management templates, aspects, policy templates, performances graphs, troubleshooting tools, auto remediation flows, and topology-based event correlation (TBEC) rules.</p>
<p>To install management packs after the first configuration, run <code>opr-mp-installer.sh</code>. For details about how to run OBM command-line tools from within the container, see the Administer section - Access-Command-Line-Interfaces topic.</p>
<p><code>opr-mp-installer</code> by default installs management packs from the <code>/opt/HP/BSM/opr/mgmtpacks </code>directory inside the OBM container. In this directory, you can find all management packs that can be selected during the suite installation.</p>
<p>Once installed, management packs cannot be removed.</p>
<p><b>Note</b>: To update a management pack to a later version than the one included with OBM, download its installation package from the Marketplace website and install the management pack manually. You can also install additional management packs that are not bundled with OBM.
</p>
<p>To install the downloaded management pack, put the management pack <b>zip</b> file (the one that contains the <code>&lt;mp_name&gt;.reg</code> file) into a location that is accessible to the OBM container. Then copy it inside the OBM container to the <code>/opt/HP/BSM/opr/mgmtpacks</code> directory and install it from there by using the <code>opr-mp-installer</code> script.</p>
<p>For example, a suitable location would be a <code>mgmtpacks</code> directory in the <code>./omi/var/opt/OV/shared/server/conf/</code> subfolder on the <code>&lt;omi-0&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;omi-1&gt;</code> volume of the NFS share. Inside <code>omi-0</code>, you can then copy the bits from <code>/var/opt/OV/shared/server/conf/mgmtpacks</code> to the <code>/opt/HP/BSM/opr/mgmtpacks</code> directory and install it from there by using the <code>opr-mp-installer</code> tool as follows: <br>
<code>/opt/HP/BSM/bin/opr-mp-installer.sh -install &lt;mp_name&gt;</code></p>
<li><p><i>Optional</i>. Configure Business Value Dashboard (BVD).</p>
<h4><span id="BVD_>_Login"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="BVD_.3E_Login">BVD &gt; Login</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=9" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: BVD > Login">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: BVD > Login">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Define the administrative user credentials for BVD. One built-in super-admin user is defined for every installation of BVD. You can later change the password in your account settings.<br>
<b><br></b>
Use suite default administrative user account<b>: Select to use the administrative user account credentials that you specified during the suite configuration.<br></b>
<b>Custom credentials: </b>Select to specify custom credentials for BVD. 
</p><p><br>
<b>Login</b>: Login name of the built-in BVD super-admin. The built-in super-admin is not listed among the users in user management. If you have logged in as the super-admin, you can change the user's information, including password and contact information, in the <b>My Account</b> page in the Personal User Settings menu. Default: admin<br>
<b>Password</b>: Password of the built-in super-admin. BVD enforces a strong password policy. The password must be at least eight characters long, and meet at least two of the following requirements: one upper-case letter, one digit, and one special character. Special characters should be ASCII characters only.<br>
<b>Confirm password:</b> Re-enter your password.
</p>
<h4><span id="BVD_>_Database"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="BVD_.3E_Database">BVD &gt; Database</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=10" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: BVD > Database">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: BVD > Database">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Configure a database to store all BVD related information. You can choose to use the database specified for the <span class="_HPc_Basic_Variables_HP_Product_Name">Operations Bridge Suite</span>, create a new, embedded database, or you can connect to an already existing database.<br>
<b>Use suite default database</b>: Select to use the database that you specified during the suite configuration. If you chose an external database, enter a database name.<br>
<b>Custom database for BVD related data: </b>Select to specify an existing, already configured database for BVD. To migrate data from a previous BVD installation, make sure you performed the migration steps described in the BVD database requirements. Then you can proceed with specifying the external PostgreSQL database that you used for your former deployment. <span>Before connecting to an external PostgreSQL database, make sure the database is installed as required by BVD.</span></p>
<p><b>Database type</b>: Choose the type of database to be used.<br>
External PostgreSQL: for use with an external PostgreSQL database.<br>
Internal PostgreSQL: for use with the embedded PostgreSQL database.<br>
<b>Host</b>: The name of the host machine on which PostgreSQL is installed. Default: localhost<br>
<b>Port</b>: The PostgreSQL listening port. Default: 5432<br>
<b>Database</b>: The name of the PostgreSQL database.<br>
<b>Login</b>: The name of a user with administrative permissions on the PostgreSQL database. Default: dbadmin<br>
<b>Password</b>: The password of the BVD administrative user to access the PostgreSQL database.<br>
</p>
</li>

<li><p>Optional. ITOM Intelligent Data Lake</p>
<h4><span id="ITOM_Intelligent_Data_Lake_>_Vertica_Connection"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="ITOM_Intelligent_Data_Lake_.3E_Vertica_Connection">ITOM Intelligent Data Lake &gt; Vertica Connection</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=11" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ITOM Intelligent Data Lake > Vertica Connection">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: ITOM Intelligent Data Lake > Vertica Connection">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Define the Vertica database details. <br>
<b>Vertica in a pre-configured container</b>: Select this option if you have a pre-configured container of Vertica. This option is suitable for evaluations.<br>
<b>Vertica DBA pasword:</b> Enter the password for the Vertica database.<br>
<b>Confirm Vertica DBA password:</b> Retype the password for the Vertica database. <br>

<b>Dedicated Vertica installation:</b> Select this option if you have a dedicated Vertica database. This option is recommended for production installations.
For dedicated Vertica installation, you need to fill the following fields:<br>
<b>Vertica Hostname:</b> Enter the Vertica hostname. For Vertica Cluster, enter the host names separated with comma(,). The format is hostname1, hostname2, hostname3.<br>
<b>Port:</b> Enter the Vertica port number.<br>
<b>Database name:</b> Enter the Vertica database name. <br>
<b>Enable TLS:</b> Select this check box if you want to enable TLS for the Vertica database.<br>
<b>Upload the CA Certificate file:</b> Click <b>Browse</b> and select the CA certificate file.<br>

<b>Kafka streaming configuration</b><br>
<b>Note</b>: The following fields can have alphabets, numbers or underscores (_) as values.<br>
<b>Resource Pool name:</b> Name of the resource pool to be created on Vertica. Resource pool is a pre-allocated subset of the system resources with an associated queue. The default value is <code>opsbridge_resource_pool</code>.<br>
<b>Scheduler name:</b> Name of the scheduler to be created on Vertica. Scheduler is responsible for streaming data load from Kafka to your Vertica database. The default value is <code>opsbridge_kafka</code>.<br>
<b>Use additional scheduler for topology:</b> Select this check box if you use an additional scheduler for topology. <br>
<b>Topology scheduler name:</b> Name of the explicit scheduler for topology to be created on Vertica. Scheduler is responsible of streaming topology data load from Kafka into your Vertica database.  <br>
<b>Note:</b> The above field is only enabled when you select the <b>Use additional scheduler for topology</b> check box.
</p>
<h4><span id="ITOM_Intelligent_Data_Lake_>_Vertica_Users"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="ITOM_Intelligent_Data_Lake_.3E_Vertica_Users">ITOM Intelligent Data Lake &gt; Vertica Users</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=12" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ITOM Intelligent Data Lake > Vertica Users">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: ITOM Intelligent Data Lake > Vertica Users">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Define the Vertica user information in this page. The database username is auto populated if you have a pre-configured container of Vertica otherwise you need to type the username of the Vertica configured in the dedicated Vertica database.<br>
<b>Database user for Data Access (Read only)</b><br>
<b>Database username:</b> Vertica database user name<br>
<b>Database password:</b> Type the Vertica database password.<br>
<b>Confirm Database password:</b> Retype the Vertica database password.</p>
<p><b>Database user for Data Producer (Read and Write)</b><br>
<b>Database username:</b> Vertica database user name<br>
<b>Database password:</b> Type the Vertica database password.<br>
<b>Confirm Database password:</b> Retype the Vertica database password.</p>
<h4><span id="ITOM_Intelligent_Data_Lake_>_Time_zone"></span><span class="mw-headline" id="ITOM_Intelligent_Data_Lake_.3E_Time_zone">ITOM Intelligent Data Lake &gt; Time zone</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=13" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: ITOM Intelligent Data Lake > Time zone">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DeCoOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: ITOM Intelligent Data Lake > Time zone">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>
<p>Select and configure the time zone for data access and rollup of data. The data from the Vertica database will be rolled-up according to the time zone you configure here.
</p><p><b>Use database time zone:</b> The time zone selected in Vertica database will be used in rollup data. This option is selected by default.
</p><p><b>Configure time zone:</b> Select to configure the time zone as required for data rollup. The data will be rolled-up according to this time zone.<br> 
</p>
<ul><li><b>Select region/time zone:</b> Select the region or the time zone from the drop-down list.<br></li>
<li><b>Select city:</b> Select the city according to the selected region or time zone. The list is displayed based on the region/time zone selected. </li></ul>
</li><li><p>On the Configuration Complete page, click <b>Next</b> to start the installation.<br>
<span>Do not refresh the page during the installation; otherwise, you will quit the installation and log out of the</span> <span class="OpsB_Suite_installationSharedServices_MgmtPortal">Management Portal</span> <span>.</span> </p>
<p>Wait until the installation is complete.</p></li>
</ol>

